  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• We obtain finite-size effects on the Bose–Einstein condensation critical temperature. • The setting is the general anisotropic harmonic trap. • We extend the known analytical first order result to higher orders. • The new results are very accurate throughout a wide regime. • These results are particularly important for low particle numbers.</subfield>
